<div>

<li>Hazard: Risk of fire, electric shock and injury if used incorrectly.</li>
<li>Do not use if plug or cord is damaged</li>
<li>Only for indoor use</li>
<li>Do not have it accesible to children</li>
<li>Always keep humidifier away from heat sources</li>

<a href="#home">Click to return to Home</a></p1>
</div>



<div id="roomplace">
<h2>Directions for Placement</h2>
<h3>Follow these steps to safely place the Holmes humidifier in your home</h3>
<h4> For extra help, please refer to the diagram 1a.</h4>
<p><img src="diagram.png" alt="diagram showing where to place" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;">></p>
</div>

<div>
 <ul class="container">
<a>1. Pick an open area in your home that is out of common pathways.</a><br>
<a>2. Pick a firm, flat level surface.</a><br>
<a>3. Make sure the desired surface is at least 4 inches (10cm) away from the nearest wall.</a><br>
<a>4. The future pathway of the cord to the electrical outlet should not be near any heat registers such as radiators, heaters, or even stoves.</a><br>
<a>5. Use both hands to place humidifier full of water on desired surface.</a><br>
<a>6. Place cord on top of any rugs.</a><br>
<a>7. Plug the humidifier directly into a 120V electrical outlet.</a><br>
<a>8. Enjoy. When you are finished, unplug and allow it to cool completely before moving.</a>
</div>



<h3>Adjusting the setup</h3>
<p><img src="inoutlet.png" alt="humidifier inlet and outlet not blocked" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"></p>
<div>

<li>Make sure there is nothing blocking the air inlet or moisture outlet</li>
<li>Position so that the moisture outlet is not facing the wall; it can cause damage to wallpaper (positioning can be seen in 1a).</li>

</div>


<p><img src="moisturemeter.png" alt="humidity meter" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"></p>
<h3>Excessive Humidity Warning</h3>
<p>Keep humidifier on only until sufficient moistness is achieved, then turn off. Excessive humidity can cause water condensation on windows or furniture and may cause damage.</p>
<div>
</div>

<div id="other">
</div>
<p><a href="#home">Click to return to Home</a></p>
<br><br>
<h2>Other Important Information</h2>

<li> Consider placing a waterproof mat or pad underneath humidifier to prevent water damage.</li>
<li>Never place humidifier on rug or carpet.</li>
<li>Do not use in closed rooms.</li>
<li>Do not drop foreign or domestic objects into inlet or outlet.</li>
<li>Misuse may result in fire, shock,or injury. </li>

